training_organizations.name: California Regional Training Academies
training_organizations.description: California funds several Regional Training Academies (at UC Davis, CSU Fresno, San Francisco State, and San Diego State) that provide standardized training to county child welfare workers statewide. These university-based centers deliver new worker core training and advanced courses to ensure consistent CPS practice across California’s counties.

training_organizations.name: Los Angeles County DCFS Training Division
training_organizations.description: The training arm of LA County’s Department of Children and Family Services, responsible for preparing the county’s CPS staff. It operates a Child Welfare Institute that offers new social worker training, supervision training, and specialized courses (e.g. forensic interviewing, trauma-informed care) to the nation’s largest local child welfare workforce.

training_organizations.name: California CASA Association
training_organizations.description: A statewide nonprofit that supports and coordinates Court Appointed Special Advocate programs across California. CASA volunteers are trained and managed by local CASA organizations (under this association’s guidance) to advocate for foster children in court, ensuring the children’s needs and best interests are heard in dependency proceedings.

policies.AntiDiscrim_Staff_VarySpecify: (1) Age, race, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, disability, religion, national origin, marital status, color, ancestry, sex, genetic information, medical condition, and ethnic group identification are specified for are specified for staff from child welfare agency contracted child welfare provider organizations; (2) Domestic partnership, political beliefs or affiliations, citizenship, and immigration status are specified for staff from child welfare agency; (3) HIV status and perceived race are not specified in state document regarding which child welfare staff and providers must abide by state law
